  "market_context": "On 25 April 2024, ES1! had a higher-time-frame imbalance (fair value gap) identified on the hourly chart between a swing high and swing low. Sell-side liquidity rested below, and SMT divergence was observed at the highs. London swept a previous high before reversing, setting up a New York reversal profile.",
  "key_observation": "A higher-time-frame fair value gap (imbalance) existed on the hourly chart. London took out a prior high then reversed, and New York made a manipulation run lower into the HTF objective (the gap), followed by displacement and close above an order block, signaling a reversal higher toward equal highs.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the hourly chart, the analyst identified a reversal structure with SMT divergence at the highs and sell-side liquidity resting below (~5036/5028 area), plus a higher-time-frame fair value gap between a defined swing high and swing low.",
    "Step 2: The analyst noted the HTF imbalance (gap) as the key objective for price to reach before reversing, framing the overall bearish-to-bullish reversal setup.",
    "Step 3: Dropping to the 15-minute chart, the analyst observed that London took out a previous high (up-close candle), then got a change in the state of delivery (close below London's range), confirming London's role in the New York reversal profile.",
    "Step 4: At 8:30 New York open, the analyst identified a manipulation move lower (the wick down) into the HTF fair value gap objective, sweeping sell-side liquidity.",
    "Step 5: Price then displaced back above and closed over the order block in that zone, providing a valid long entry off the order block.",
    "Step 6: The analyst identified equal highs above as the target for the reversal move, and confirmed price rallied to reach those equal highs, completing the New York reversal profile."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price reversed higher from the HTF fair value gap / order block entry after the 8:30 New York manipulation sweep, rallying to the equal highs above — confirming the New York reversal profile played out successfully.",
  "lessons": "When a higher-time-frame fair value gap exists and London fails to reach it, New York will often extend into that HTF objective as a manipulation move before reversing. An order block entry at the HTF imbalance, confirmed by SMT divergence and a change in state of delivery, provides a high-probability New York reversal trade.",
